                            <comment id="429821" author="adilger" created="Tue, 1 Oct 2024 20:36:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17962&quot; title=&quot;conf-sanity test_32a: failed with replace_nids operation already in progress&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-17962&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-17962&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="429816" author="adilger" created="Tue, 1 Oct 2024 20:11:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is really a leak on the &lt;b&gt;client&lt;/b&gt; after running interop testing with sanity-flr (full-part-1) so it couldn&apos;t have anything to do with mmp (which only runs testing on the servers).  It is really a bug somewhere in sanity-flr that is not noticed in that test script since it isn&apos;t unmounting the filesystem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would make sense to add a cleanupall/setupall at the end of sanity-flr to isolate this failure there.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="417551" author="sarah" created="Wed, 12 Jun 2024 21:52:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/9719647e-32c7-4f85-8c32-076f30b08597&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/9719647e-32c7-4f85-8c32-076f30b08597&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
